snippet.textDisplay:
G'day,

Yay Team !

To be serious...

If you title-search my Videos, or my "Weird Things in Daily Life On An Endangered Species Sanctuary..." Playlist ; for,

"Drop Bear Attacks Weather Station..!"

Thereinat you will find the Origin of the "Drop Bear" Myth unveiled.

A Sugar Glider landed on my Anenometer, Weather-Vane & Rainguage in the dark, apparently mistaking it for a Tree..., alighting hard enough to have broken the Equipment.

As I was repairing & rebuilding the Anenometer I realised that if a Townie, a Citibred Suburbanite, or Foreign Tourist was to go outside for a Piss at night - and have a Sugar Glider land on their Head, with a Pawful of Claws at each Corner & a big fluffy Tail, scrabbling to jump off again because it was terrified when the supposed "Shrub" turned out to be an equally terrified Human...; then by the time the Person has recovered their wits the Sugar Glider has long gone - back into the Darkness, climbing into the Canopy, going up the nearest Tree.

Koalas do not DROP onto people, but Sugar Gliders fly at night & they have a 1 to 1 Glide Ratio - they come down quite steep & fast, and quarter or half a Kilogram of furry Meat with Claws arriving at 10 Km/Hr on your Head will feel pretty big & scary, afterwards.

So, there you go, and now you know ; Mystery Solved...

Such is Life,

Have a good one.

;-p

Ciao !
